<doc id="322648" wikidata="Q131972" url="?curid=322648" title="Hoplocercidae">
<text>Hoplocercidae are a family of lizards native to the tropical forests, woodlands and savanna-like habitats of Central and South America. Alternatively they are recognized as a subfamily, Hoplocercinae. 20 species in two genera are described.

==Species==

